Odaily Planet Daily News According to the monitoring of on-chain analyst Yu Jin, after Binance launched Mubarak spot today, an address transferred 11 million Mubarak (US$1.49 million) to Binance. He earned 1.6 million (+1075%) on Mubarak. In general, the address spent a total of US$149,000 to buy Mubarak at a price of US$0.011 and sold it at a price of US$0.135. Specifically: 
The address spent a total of US$149,000 to buy 13 million Mubaraks between March 14 and 16, with an average price of US$0.011; 
Sold 2 million (US$266,000) through Bitget at a price of US$0.133 6 days ago; 
Another 11 million were all transferred to Binance at a price of US$0.135 after Binance launched spot.

1. Arthur Hayes: April will be a turning point for the market, and a new round of market growth is coming;
2. Insider: The US SEC has officially ended its investigation into Crypto.com;
3. Binance will launch four tokens and trading pairs including MUBARAK;
4. The third fund under the crypto venture capital Maven 11 has completed fundraising of US$107 million;
5. Hyperliquid: Will compensate JELLY long users and strengthen platform risk management;
6. Paul Atkins confirmed the nomination of SEC Chairman and promised to bring transparency and regulatory clarity to the crypto industry;
7. A whale transferred 8.7 million LAYER to Binance, and the sale will make a profit of US$4.63 million;
8. South Carolina withdraws the pledge lawsuit against Coinbase;
9. The US Department of Justice seized US$200,000 in crypto assets related to Hamas;
10. Tencent invested 1.16 billion euros in Ubisoft's new subsidiary 25%, the transaction is expected to be completed before the end of the year;
11. Sei Foundation plans to acquire 23andMe.

Odaily Planet Daily News: OpenAI founder Sam Altman wrote that the new version of GPT-4o is particularly good at coding, following instructions, and freedom. Previously, OpenAI wrote that GPT-4o was updated again in ChatGPT, and the new changes are as follows: 
Better at following detailed instructions, especially prompts with multiple requests; 
Improved ability to handle complex technical and coding problems; ·Enhanced intuition and creativity; 
Reduce the use of emoticons.
